grade. For example, among children in Std III, 7.8% cannot even read a letter, 19.3% can read a letter but not a word, 14.8% can read a word but not a Std I level text, 19.3% can read a Std I level text but not a Std II level text, and 38.8% can read a Std II level text. For each grade, the total of these exclusive categories is 100%.

