This graph shows the progress of three cohorts from Std III to Std VII. For example, the first cohort was in Std III in 2008, in Std V in 2010, and in Std VII in 2012. For this cohort: % children who were at subtraction level in Std III (in 2008) was 45%, and in Std V (in 2010) was 75%. When the cohort reached Std VII in 2012, this figure was 65%. The progress of each of these cohorts can be understood in the same way.

