In most states, children are expected to do 2-digit by 2-digit subtraction with borrowing by Std II. Table 7 shows the proportion of children in Std III who can do subtraction. This figure is a proxy for "grade level" arithmetic for Std III. Data for children enrolled in government schools and private schools is shown separately.

